\date{2024-04-02}
\title{sieve}
\author{trebor}
\taxon{Definition}
\import{common}

\p{
  A \strong{sieve} over an object #{A} of an arbitrary category #{\CatVar{C}} is a subfunctor of #{\yo(A)}. More explicitly, it selects some arrows with codomain #{A}, such that the selected arrows absorbs composition (i.e. if #{f : B \to A} is selected and #{g : C \to B}, then #{g \compose f} is also selected).
}
